{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The fine-tuning parameters for WMT21fb model are the same as the NLLB-200-distilled, except for the batch size value which is set as 2.",
    "This is because the model is too large that we get outof-memory (OOM) errors if we increase the batch size larger than 2.",
    "More details on M2M-100 parameters and layer settings for Conditional Generation Structure (55) we used for xL-MPLM WMT21fb and NLLB-200 can be found in Appendix Figure A2.",
    "The evaluation corpus we used is from the ClinSpEn-2022 shared task challenge data organised as part of the Biomedical MT track in WMT2022 (25).",
    "It has three sub-tasks: The automatic evaluation metrics used for testing include BLEU (HuggingFace) (56), ROUGE-L-F1 (57), METEOR (58), SACREBLEU (59), and COMET (60), hosted by the ClinSpEn-2022 platform."
  ],
